- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language generation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a system for automatic generation of natural language descriptions. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper mentions machine learning approaches and the use of a repository of natural language sentences. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper discusses the difficulty in presenting computational results to non-expert users. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a system for generating natural language descriptions for applications targeting mainstream users.
